headline: 2 Reasons to Like CAH (and 1 Not So Much)
summary: Since April 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 87.2%. But one standout stock has nearly doubled the market - over the past five years, Cardinal Health has surged 159% to $127.74 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 13.4% in the last six months thanks to its solid quarterly results, beating the S&P by 23.9%.
